OL,3,CWigan Warriors legend Billy Boston
OL,4,Cknighted at Buckingham Palace
OL,6,FThe 90-year-old, who was born in
OL,7,FWales, played on the wing at Wigan for
OL,8,F15 years after making the switch from
OL,9,Frugby union to rugby league in 1953.
OL,11,FHe went on to score a record 478 tries
OL,12,Fin 487 games for the club winning the
OL,13,FChallenge Cup three times as well as
OL,14,Fthe Championship.
OL,16,FAt a ceremony at Buckingham Palace,
OL,17,FKing Charles bestowed the knighthood
OL,18,Fon the 90-year-old, who now lives with
OL,19,Fdementia.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
