OL,3,CWigan Warriors legend Billy Boston
OL,4,Cknighted at Buckingham Palace
OL,6,FBoston also had an impressive record
OL,7,Ffor Great Britain scoring 24 tries in
OL,8,F31 test matches and in 1954 became the
OL,9,Ffirst non-white player selected to
OL,10,Ftour Australia and New Zealand.
OL,12,FIn 2000, he was given the freedom of
OL,13,FWigan and has three statues, in Wigan,
OL,14,FWales and at Wembley Stadium.
OL,16,FBoston was awarded an MBE by Queen
OL,17,FElizabeth and now, after a campaign
OL,18,Fled by his local Makerfield MP Josh
OL,19,FSimons, he was made a knight of the
OL,20,Frealm by King Charles.
